WEBVTT

00:02.132 --> 00:03.699
-PREVIOUSLY ON "OUTSIDERS"...

00:03.829 --> 00:06.484
-IT SEEMS THAT DEPUTY HOUGHTON
IS UNDER A LOT OF STRESS.

00:06.615 --> 00:08.443
OXYCONTIN, ISN'T IT?

00:10.401 --> 00:11.750
-YOU BE SOBER TOMORROW,

00:11.881 --> 00:13.274
BECAUSE I AM GONNA
TAKE YOU BY THE HAND

00:13.404 --> 00:14.927
AND LEAD YOU UP THAT HILL.

00:15.058 --> 00:17.408
THIS IS RIDICULOUS,
THE CRAP I GOTTA PUT UP WITH.

00:17.539 --> 00:19.280
[ CLICK ]
AAH! [ GRUNTING ] DAMN IT! SHIT!

00:19.410 --> 00:20.803
-BOSS...
-UHH! AAH!

00:20.933 --> 00:22.761
[ SLICES ]
-UGH!

00:22.892 --> 00:25.068
-THEM FARRELLS, THEY DON'T OWN
THAT LAND THEY LIVE ON.

00:25.199 --> 00:26.635
I JUST GOTTA WONDER WHY

00:26.765 --> 00:28.811
WE GOTTA PLAY BY THE RULES
AND THEM FARRELLS DON'T.

00:28.941 --> 00:31.596
-DO YOU LOVE HIM?
-I DO.

00:34.338 --> 00:36.775
-[ HACKING COUGH ]

00:36.906 --> 00:38.603
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

00:38.734 --> 00:41.606
HOW LONG...I BEEN AWAY?

00:41.737 --> 00:43.565
-13 DAYS.
-AAH!

00:43.695 --> 00:46.089
I KNOW WHAT YOU DID.

00:46.220 --> 00:48.135
-IT'S CALLED A DRONE.

00:48.265 --> 00:49.614
WELL, THEY CAN PROGRAM
THESE THINGS

00:49.745 --> 00:51.225
TO FLY UP HERE
AND TAKE PICTURES.

00:51.355 --> 00:52.704
CAN YOU FIX IT?

00:52.835 --> 00:55.142
-I CAN, BUT I UNDERSTAND
YOU FOLKS,

00:55.272 --> 00:56.969
YOU DON'T DEAL IN CASH.

00:57.100 --> 00:59.450
♪♪

01:08.285 --> 01:11.027
♪♪

01:11.158 --> 01:13.551
[ DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE ]

01:13.682 --> 01:16.163
[ SNIPPING ]

01:26.521 --> 01:27.783
[ SNIPS ]

01:27.913 --> 01:30.351
♪♪

01:38.098 --> 01:40.274
-[ BREATHING NERVOUSLY ]

01:45.975 --> 01:47.977
-NO, NO, DON'T --
-YOU DON'T NEED TO SEE THE REST.

01:48.108 --> 01:49.935
-WELL, GEE,
IT WAS JUST GETTIN' GOOD.

01:50.066 --> 01:52.242
-EXCUSE ME.
THIS IS FUNNY TO YOU?

01:52.373 --> 01:54.549
-I WOULDN'T SAY FUNNY.
REVEALING, MORE THAN ANYTHING.

01:54.679 --> 01:56.203
-DAMN IT, HAYLIE!

01:56.333 --> 01:57.900
MY FAMILY AND MY PRIVACY
HAS BEEN INVADED.

01:58.030 --> 01:59.510
-AND?

01:59.641 --> 02:00.946
-AND WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO
ABOUT IT?

02:01.077 --> 02:02.861
-IT'S NOT WHAT WE'RE GONNA
DO ABOUT IT, NED.

02:02.992 --> 02:04.298
IT'S WHAT YOU'RE GONNA DO
ABOUT IT,

02:04.428 --> 02:06.169
WHICH WOULD BE TO GROW A PAIR.

02:06.300 --> 02:08.171
THIS IS NOT A BUSINESS
FOR LITTLE GIRLS.

02:08.302 --> 02:09.999
'CAUSE IT'S NOT A BUSINESS.
IT'S A WAR.

02:10.130 --> 02:11.827
BUT AS WITH ANY WAR,

02:11.957 --> 02:14.308
THE EVENTUAL VICTOR'S GONNA
TAKE SOME DAMAGE ALONG THE WAY.

02:14.438 --> 02:16.527
YOUR CHERISHED PRIVACY,
FOR EXAMPLE.

02:16.658 --> 02:18.877
AND IF THAT'S TOO BIG
OF A SACRIFICE FOR YOU,

02:19.008 --> 02:21.358
I SUGGEST YOU PULL UP YOUR SKIRT
AND RUN ALONG.

02:21.489 --> 02:23.708
-WAIT A MINUTE.
YOU'RE NOT GONNA HELP ME?

02:23.839 --> 02:25.449
THIS IS OF NO INTEREST TO YOU?

02:25.580 --> 02:28.409
-OH, I AM INTERESTED. I WOULD
LOVE TO KNOW WHO DID THIS.

02:28.539 --> 02:30.367
-WELL, IT HAS TO BE
THE FARRELLS.

02:30.498 --> 02:32.021
I MEAN, WE LOST THE DRONE
UP THERE.

02:32.152 --> 02:33.631
THEY FOUND IT AND DID THIS.

02:33.762 --> 02:35.720
-YES, NED, THEY'RE KNOWN FOR
THEIR TECHNICAL APTITUDE.

02:35.851 --> 02:37.548
THESE PEOPLE SHIT OUTDOORS.

02:37.679 --> 02:38.897
YOU REALLY THINK THEY'D BE ABLE
TO OPERATE THATTHING

02:39.028 --> 02:40.725
WITHOUT A CONTROLLER?

02:40.856 --> 02:43.554
-I DIDN'T THINK ABOUT THAT.

02:43.685 --> 02:45.643
SO THEN WHO WAS IT?

02:45.774 --> 02:47.863
-I HAVE NO IDEA.
BUT THEY'RE SMART.

02:47.993 --> 02:50.082
YOU DON'T FIND THAT SO MUCH
AROUND HERE.

02:50.213 --> 02:52.215
DOESN'T MATTER.
I LIKE A CHALLENGE.

02:53.608 --> 02:56.611
♪♪

03:02.747 --> 03:04.880
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

03:15.369 --> 03:17.197
-I DON'T KNOW WHO MADE
THIS COFFEE,

03:17.327 --> 03:20.417
BUT IT'S BETTER WHEN YOU START
OFF WITH WATER INSTEAD OF PISS.

03:20.548 --> 03:22.071
[ LAUGHTER ]
-IT'S GODDAMN FOUL.

03:24.421 --> 03:26.293
I HOPE YOUR WOMAN MADE YOU
SOMETHING TO EAT.

03:26.423 --> 03:28.469
THERE AIN'T HARDLY NOTHING LEFT
HERE BUT SHADOWS.

03:28.599 --> 03:31.776
-SHE AIN'T GONNA BE MY WOMAN
THAT MUCH LONGER.

03:31.907 --> 03:33.256
SHE GONNA BE MY WIFE.

03:33.387 --> 03:34.518
-[ MAN CHUCKLES ]

03:34.649 --> 03:35.780
[ MURMURING ]

03:35.911 --> 03:37.869
-GED-GEDYAH.

03:38.000 --> 03:40.045
WHAT YOU GOTTA SAY ABOUT THAT?

03:40.176 --> 03:43.962
-WELL, I SAY IT AIN'T RIGHT THAT
A MAN STARTS THE DAY OUT DRUNK.

03:44.093 --> 03:46.138
YOU WANNA TALK NONSENSE,
YOU GO TELL THE TREES.

03:46.269 --> 03:48.271
[ SCATTERED LAUGHS ]
-GO ON, LAUGH IT UP.

03:48.402 --> 03:51.622
Y'ALL GONNA SEE ME RUNNING
THE GAUNTLET ON MY WEDDING DAY.

03:51.753 --> 03:53.755
-WHEN'S THIS HAPPENING?

03:53.885 --> 03:55.452
-DON'T KNOW. SOON.

03:55.583 --> 03:56.801
-UH-HUH.

03:56.932 --> 03:59.761
-W-WE GOT THINGS TO DO,

03:59.891 --> 04:03.243
SEE LADY RAY AND GET BLESSINGS.

04:03.373 --> 04:05.810
-WHY NOW?
-HOW'S THAT?

04:05.941 --> 04:08.378
-WELL, WHY DO YOU THINK
SHE WANTS TO MARRY UP NOW?

04:08.509 --> 04:10.424
ALL THE YEARS YOU SHARE A BED,

04:10.554 --> 04:14.254
ALL THE TIMES YOU ASKED,
SHE SAID NO.

04:14.384 --> 04:16.560
WHAT CHANGED?

04:16.691 --> 04:17.996
-WHY YOU DOING THIS?

04:18.127 --> 04:19.824
-I'M JUST SPECULATIN'.

04:19.955 --> 04:22.262
-WHY CAN'T YOU GIVE ME
CONGRATULATIONS?

04:22.392 --> 04:24.176
YOU'RE THE FIRST PERSON
I COME TO SEE,

04:24.307 --> 04:26.353
AND YOU JUST START TWISTIN' IT.

04:26.483 --> 04:29.269
SEE HOW YOU FEEL WHEN I STOP
COMIN' ROUND YOU NO MORE.

04:30.618 --> 04:33.011
-SON. HEY. HEY, SON!

04:37.189 --> 04:39.061
I'M SORRY.

04:41.846 --> 04:43.152
COME HERE.

04:47.025 --> 04:50.420
I AM PROUD OF YOU, SON.

04:53.989 --> 04:57.297
SHE IS A FINE, FINE WOMAN.

04:57.427 --> 05:00.561
YOU JUST -- YOU TREAT HER RIGHT,

05:00.691 --> 05:03.477
'CAUSE I DON'T WANNA SEE YOU
LOSING HER

05:03.607 --> 05:05.217
TO SOME OTHER MAN.

05:05.348 --> 05:08.264
♪♪

05:08.395 --> 05:09.787
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

05:09.918 --> 05:12.312
♪♪

05:16.403 --> 05:17.882
-WHOO!

05:18.013 --> 05:21.059
LOOKS LIKE SOMEBODY
GOT THEMSELVES A JOB!

05:21.190 --> 05:24.062
WHO'D YOU BLOW, BREECE?
-YEAH.

05:24.193 --> 05:25.934
♪♪

05:31.418 --> 05:33.289
-CAN I HELP YOU?
-[ SIGHS ] HOPE SO.

05:33.420 --> 05:34.943
UM, MY NAME IS BREECE DOBBS.

05:35.073 --> 05:36.727
I'M SUPPOSED TO BE STARTING
WORK HERE TODAY.

05:36.858 --> 05:39.469
I'M THE COMMUNITY LIAISON.
-MM.

05:39.600 --> 05:41.776
-UM, IS MISS GRIMES AVAILABLE?

05:41.906 --> 05:44.344
-SHE SHOULD BE BACK SOON.
WOULD YOU MIND WAITING?

05:44.474 --> 05:45.910
-SURE.

05:54.789 --> 05:56.660
[ DISTANT TELEPHONE RINGING ]

05:56.791 --> 05:58.575
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

05:58.706 --> 06:00.403
-KNOCK, KNOCK.

06:00.534 --> 06:03.363
NICE UNIFORM.

06:03.493 --> 06:04.973
-OH, YEAH? YOU LIKE THIS?

06:05.103 --> 06:07.410
-I DO.

06:07.541 --> 06:09.673
-IT WAS TOM WEINEKE'S FUNERAL
THIS MORNING.

06:09.804 --> 06:11.545
-I KNOW.

06:11.675 --> 06:14.765
I CALLED MRS. WEINEKE LAST NIGHT
TO PASS ALONG MY CONDOLENCES.

06:14.896 --> 06:18.465
SUCH A TERRIBLE STORY.
IT'S JUST AWFUL.

06:18.595 --> 06:20.945
WELL, THIS IS JUST
A LITTLE SOMETHING.

06:21.076 --> 06:24.645
THE USUAL --
SNACKS, PRETZELS, CHIPS.

06:24.775 --> 06:26.951
-MM-HMM.

06:27.082 --> 06:29.998
-I REALLY ENJOYED
WORKING WITH TOM.

06:30.128 --> 06:31.565
HOPEFULLY YOU AND I CAN
WORK TOGETHER

06:31.695 --> 06:33.305
TO MAKE SURE
THAT PROGRESS CONTINUES

06:33.436 --> 06:35.177
WITHOUT ANY FURTHER DELAYS.

06:35.307 --> 06:37.484
-YOU COULD'VE JUST SAID THAT
WITH SO MUCH LESS WORDS,

06:37.614 --> 06:39.660
COULDN'T YOU?

06:39.790 --> 06:41.618
I MEAN, LIKE,
"HERE'S A BASKET OF SHIT.

06:41.749 --> 06:43.446
NOW DO WHAT I TELL YOU."

06:43.577 --> 06:45.927
-[ CHUCKLES ]

06:46.057 --> 06:48.320
YOU HAVE A BETTER SENSE OF HUMOR
THAN TOM DID, THAT'S FOR SURE.

06:48.451 --> 06:50.627
-YEAH, I MEAN, I THINK
IT WAS YOU WHO KILLED HIM,

06:50.758 --> 06:52.324
WHEN ALL IS SAID AND DONE.

06:52.455 --> 06:56.024
YOU AND YOUR BOSSES.
YOU DROVE HIM UP THAT MOUNTAIN.

06:56.154 --> 07:00.071
YOU PUSHED AND YOU PROVOKED HIM
TILL IT COST HIM HIS LIFE.

07:00.202 --> 07:03.684
-WELL, I OBVIOUSLY
SHOULDN'T HAVE COME TODAY.

07:03.814 --> 07:06.208
IT'S AN EMOTIONAL MORNING,
I'M SURE.

07:14.521 --> 07:17.045
-HEARD THE HAPPY NEWS.

07:17.175 --> 07:19.526
THOUGHT PERHAPS YOU MIGHT'VE
TOLD ME IN PERSON.

07:19.656 --> 07:21.919
MAYBE THE LAST TIME
WE MADE LOVE.

07:22.050 --> 07:23.834
I MEAN, THAT WOULD'VE BEEN
A GOOD TIME.

07:23.965 --> 07:26.750
-IS THAT WHAT WAS ON YOUR MIND?

07:26.881 --> 07:28.752
MAKING LOVE?

07:30.188 --> 07:32.843
-WELL, YOU KNOW ME, G'WIN.
I'M A ROMANTIC.

07:32.974 --> 07:37.892
ALWAYS HAVE BEEN, EVER SINCE
WE WERE FIRST TOGETHER.

07:38.022 --> 07:40.851
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE ACTUALLY DOING THIS.

07:40.982 --> 07:44.072
-DOING WHAT?
-MAKING A HUGE MISTAKE.

07:44.202 --> 07:47.205
-YEAH, ANY WOMAN DON'T WANNA END
UP WITH THE GREAT ASA FARRELL,

07:47.336 --> 07:48.772
OF COURSE SHE'S MAKING
A MISTAKE.

07:48.903 --> 07:50.382
YOU GOT SUCH A HIGH VIEW
OF YOURSELF.

07:50.513 --> 07:52.689
IT'S WHY YOU RUN OFF
10 YEARS AGO.

07:52.820 --> 07:55.518
YOU'RE TOO SPECIAL
FOR THIS PLACE AND THESE PEOPLE.

07:55.649 --> 07:58.303
-THE WORLD'S BIGGER THAN THIS
MOUNTAIN, G'WIN. YOU KNOW THAT.

07:58.434 --> 08:01.481
-YOU'RE TOO SPECIAL FOR ME.

08:01.611 --> 08:05.267
WAKE UP TO YOURSELF, ASA.
YOU'RE NOT SPECIAL.

08:05.397 --> 08:09.227
YOU'RE JUST A MAN.
-OKAY, I GOT IT.

08:09.358 --> 08:12.100
AND I JUST WANNA SAY
FROM THE BOTTOM OF MY HEART

08:12.230 --> 08:14.755
THAT I AM SO SORRY.

08:14.885 --> 08:16.278
-FOR WHAT?

08:16.408 --> 08:20.412
-FOR LEAVING,
BECAUSE I HAD NO IDEA

08:20.543 --> 08:23.285
THESE WERE THE DEPTHS
TO WHICH I HAD SCREWED YOU UP.

08:29.247 --> 08:33.251
-I SPENT THE LAST 10 YEARS
THINKING BACK,

08:33.382 --> 08:38.169
ABOUT HOW WONDERFUL IT WAS WHEN
OUR -- OUR BODIES CAME TOGETHER.

08:38.300 --> 08:41.259
AND THEN YOU RETURNED, AND OUR
BODIES CAME TOGETHER AGAIN.

08:41.390 --> 08:43.523
AND... [ INHALES DEEPLY ]

08:45.350 --> 08:47.091
IT WASN'T THAT GREAT.

08:48.745 --> 08:52.836
SEE, LIL FOSTER, HE PLEASES ME
SO MUCH BETTER.

08:58.973 --> 09:01.366
-OKAY.

09:01.497 --> 09:04.587
SEE YOU AGAIN SOON.

09:04.718 --> 09:06.937
MAYBE ON YOUR WEDDIN' NIGHT.
HMM?

09:28.872 --> 09:31.353
♪♪

09:50.851 --> 09:54.594
♪♪

09:54.724 --> 09:58.728
-♪ THE DAWN IS UP, THERE'S
FIRE ON THE MOUNTAIN ♪

09:58.859 --> 10:02.776
♪ THEY'LL HAVE TO ANSWER
FOR THEIR CROOKED PLAN ♪

10:02.906 --> 10:05.866
♪ THE HOLLOWS
WILL SURROUND THEM ♪

10:05.996 --> 10:08.216
♪ AND THEY'LL GO RUNNIN'

10:08.346 --> 10:11.611
♪ BACK TO THE WRETCHED REALM
THEY CAME ♪

10:13.830 --> 10:20.271
♪ NOR WILL THE DOGS OF HELL
REFRAIN ♪

10:20.402 --> 10:25.929
♪ AND THE LAND WILL SUFFER
THOSE WHO PAID ♪

10:39.769 --> 10:41.641
-WHAT ARE YOU DOIN' HERE?

10:41.771 --> 10:45.427
-[ SCOFFS ] WHAT'S IT LOOK LIKE?

10:45.557 --> 10:49.997
-IT'S A LITTLE EARLY IN THE DAY
FOR SHINE, FOR YOU, AIN'T IT?

10:50.127 --> 10:53.087
-OH, HE SAYS,
POURING HIMSELF A DRINK.

10:53.217 --> 10:55.176
-I SAID IT WAS EARLY FOR YOU,
LOSTIE.

10:55.306 --> 10:56.830
[ POURS LIQUOR ]

10:56.960 --> 10:58.832
-I GOT AN IDEA, FOSTER.

10:58.962 --> 11:00.355
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

11:00.485 --> 11:04.228
HOW ABOUT I PROPOSE
A LITTLE TOAST?

11:04.359 --> 11:07.188
TO LADY RAY'S
CONTINUING GOOD HEALTH.

11:07.318 --> 11:09.277
♪♪

11:09.407 --> 11:10.670
-THAT'S A RIGHT
BEAUTIFUL THOUGHT.

11:10.800 --> 11:12.497
[ GLASSES CLINK ]
-GED-GEDYAH.

11:12.628 --> 11:14.325
-GED-GEDYAH.

11:17.677 --> 11:18.982
HEY...

11:21.681 --> 11:24.553
HOW ABOUT YOU AND ME...

11:24.684 --> 11:27.034
WE PLAY US A LITTLE GAME?

11:27.164 --> 11:29.689
-OH, FORGIVE ME, FOSTER,
BUT I DON'T MUCH RELISH

11:29.819 --> 11:32.387
THE THOUGHT OF DOING ANYTHING
WITH YOU THAT INVOLVES KNIVES.

11:32.517 --> 11:36.608
-I AIN'T GONNA HURT YOU, COUSIN.
I JUST WANNA PLAY.

11:38.698 --> 11:40.743
-COME ON THEN.

11:40.874 --> 11:44.094
-MY CHILDREN, OUR FAMILY'S
TRADITIONS ARE CLEAR --

11:44.225 --> 11:48.229
ONLY DEATH RELEASES YOU
FROM YOUR MARITAL OBLIGATIONS.

11:48.359 --> 11:50.579
ARE YOU BOTH IN ACCEPTANCE?

11:50.710 --> 11:52.712
-YES, MA'AM.
-YES, MA'AM.

11:52.842 --> 11:56.890
-BUT TELL ME NOW, BOTH OF YOU...

11:57.020 --> 11:58.718
WHY DO YOU WISH TO MARRY?

11:58.848 --> 12:02.156
-WELL, MA'AM, I...

12:02.286 --> 12:04.027
THERE HASN'T BEEN A DAY
IN THE LAST 10 YEARS

12:04.158 --> 12:06.203
THAT I HAVEN'T THOUGHT ABOUT IT,

12:06.334 --> 12:07.814
WANTED IT.

12:07.944 --> 12:09.946
SHE'S MY LIFE.

12:10.077 --> 12:13.863
-10 YEAR A LONG DURATION
MAKE A MAN WAIT.

12:13.994 --> 12:16.083
WHY COULDN'T YOU MAKE
YOUR AGREE SOONER?

12:16.213 --> 12:17.519
-DON'T KNOW.

12:17.649 --> 12:22.002
MY MIND WAS CLOUDED, I GUESS,
BY...

12:22.132 --> 12:23.481
PAST EVENTS.

12:23.612 --> 12:25.266
-THE LOSS OF YOUR BABY?

12:27.137 --> 12:29.618
-YES, MA'AM.

12:29.749 --> 12:31.402
BUT MY MIND IS CLEAR NOW.

12:32.839 --> 12:35.276
I LOOK AT HIM, AND I SEE...

12:35.406 --> 12:38.583
A-A GOOD, STEADY,

12:38.714 --> 12:40.455
CARING, HONEST MAN.

12:40.585 --> 12:43.545
A MAN I WANT FOR MY HUSBAND.

12:44.720 --> 12:46.156
[ KISSES HAND ]

12:53.076 --> 12:54.904
-LET'S SEE...

12:55.035 --> 12:57.124
AW. LOOKS LIKE I GOT THAT ROUND.

12:57.254 --> 12:59.387
-NO, LOOK, THAT'S MY SECOND
THROW. IT'S CLOSEST TO THE RED.

12:59.517 --> 13:01.781
-ALL RIGHT, I STAND CORRECTED.

13:01.911 --> 13:03.652
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ] OOH.

13:07.743 --> 13:09.658
OOH. [ INHALES SHARPLY ]

13:09.789 --> 13:12.574
OH, I BETTER START DOING
SOME THROWIN'

13:12.704 --> 13:14.315
OR I'LL THROW MY BREAKFAST.

13:14.445 --> 13:17.797
-[ LAUGHS ] OKAY,
NOW THAT WAS FUNNY.

13:17.927 --> 13:20.625
-YOU JUST SHUT YOUR MOUTH
AND THROW, LOSTIE.

13:23.498 --> 13:26.327
-[ GRUNTS ]
-AH...

13:26.457 --> 13:29.199
YOU, UH, YOU HEAR
MY BOY'S GETTIN' MARRIED?

13:30.331 --> 13:32.159
IN THE BLACK, SON.

13:32.289 --> 13:34.465
YOU TAKE ANOTHER DRINK.

13:38.034 --> 13:39.949
-[ EXHALES ]
-YEAH, THAT G'WIN.

13:40.080 --> 13:43.474
I GOTTA SAY, I ALWAYS THOUGHT
SHE'D END UP WITH SOMEBODY ELSE.

13:43.605 --> 13:45.302
OH, IN THE BLACK AGAIN.

13:45.433 --> 13:47.174
IT'S NOT A GOOD ROUND FOR YOU
AT ALL.

13:47.304 --> 13:49.480
-[ CHUCKLES ]

13:49.611 --> 13:51.047
[ PANTING ]

13:52.788 --> 13:54.659
[ GLASS THUDS ]

13:54.790 --> 13:56.226
-YEAH, G'WIN.

13:56.357 --> 13:58.446
SHE KNOWS A GOOD MAN
FROM ONE WHO AIN'T SO GOOD.

13:58.576 --> 14:00.143
-COULD YOU, UH,
STOP TALKING, PLEASE?

14:00.274 --> 14:02.711
I'M TRYING TO CONCENTRATE.
-I AIN'T TALKIN'.

14:02.842 --> 14:04.365
I'M THINKING OUT LOUD. GO ON.

14:06.410 --> 14:08.064
-BEAT THAT.

14:08.195 --> 14:10.588
-YEAH.
-OOH.

14:12.677 --> 14:14.854
-NOW, UH...

14:14.984 --> 14:16.681
WHAT YOU THINK
ABOUT THEM GETTIN' MARRIED?

14:16.812 --> 14:18.945
-OH, IT'S NONE OF MY CONCERN.

14:19.075 --> 14:22.862
-I THOUGHT THAT YOU MIGHT HAVE
AN OPINION ON THE MATTER.

14:22.992 --> 14:24.646
-YOU THOUGHT WRONG.

14:24.776 --> 14:27.344
-WELL, LOOKS LIKE YOU WON AGAIN.

14:27.475 --> 14:29.825
WHY DON'T YOU FETCH THEM KNIVES?

14:29.956 --> 14:31.392
[ GLASS THUDS ]

14:35.962 --> 14:37.964
SORRY, COUSIN.

14:39.966 --> 14:41.881
APPEARS I HAD ONE MORE.

14:46.929 --> 14:48.365
-ALL RIGHT, THANKS.

14:53.109 --> 14:54.806
[ DOOR BELL JINGLES ]

14:59.986 --> 15:02.466
-HEY.
-WHAT DO YOU WANT?

15:02.597 --> 15:04.729
-WELL, I, UH... [ CHUCKLES ]

15:04.860 --> 15:07.689
WANNA APOLOGIZE ABOUT
OUR -- OUR DATE.

15:07.819 --> 15:11.214
I GOT IN A LITTLE BIT
OF TROUBLE THERE.

15:11.345 --> 15:13.173
YOU MAD?

15:13.303 --> 15:15.392
-IT'S NOT THE FIRST TIME
I'VE BEEN STOOD UP.

15:15.523 --> 15:17.699
WON'T BE THE LAST.

15:17.829 --> 15:21.224
-NOT REALLY SURE WHAT THAT
MEANS, BUT...

15:21.355 --> 15:24.532
-DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.
GOTTA GET HOME.

15:24.662 --> 15:26.882
-COME ON. YOU AIN'T --

15:27.013 --> 15:29.015
YOU AIN'T GONNA LET ME
APOLOGIZE?

15:29.145 --> 15:31.408
GOT ME A GOOD ONE WORKED OUT.

15:31.539 --> 15:32.801
HAD A LONG TIME
TO THINK ABOUT IT.

15:32.932 --> 15:34.585
-COULD YOU JUST LEAVE ME ALONE?

15:34.716 --> 15:36.326
-WHY WOULD I DO THAT?

15:36.457 --> 15:38.154
-IT'S NOT GONNA WORK, HASIL.
WE'RE TOO DIFFERENT.

15:38.285 --> 15:41.070
-WHAT YOU MEAN?
COME ON, WE'RE BOTH PEOPLE.

15:41.201 --> 15:43.203
I MEAN, SURE, YOU'RE A WOMAN,
I'M A MAN.

15:43.333 --> 15:44.856
BUT THAT SORT OF HELPS
THE SITUATION, DON'T IT?

15:44.987 --> 15:46.075
-EXCEPT I LIVE
IN THE REAL WORLD,

15:46.206 --> 15:47.424
AND YOU LIVE UP THERE.

15:47.555 --> 15:51.254
I'M BLACK, AND YOU ARE WEIRD.

15:51.385 --> 15:52.777
JUST GO AWAY.

15:52.908 --> 15:55.128
-LOOK, CAN I AT LEAST
GIVE YOU THIS?

15:55.258 --> 15:57.782
-WHAT IS IT?

15:57.913 --> 16:01.221
-WELL...MADE YOU A PRESENT,
'CAUSE TO BE HONEST WITH YOU,

16:01.351 --> 16:04.964
I KINDA KNEW MY APOLOGY WASN'T
GONNA BE THAT GOOD.

16:05.094 --> 16:07.923
COME ON, PLEASE?

16:11.535 --> 16:15.061
CAREFUL WITH IT. IT MIGHT...

16:15.191 --> 16:17.802
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

16:17.933 --> 16:21.371
YEAH.
-[ CHUCKLES ]

16:21.502 --> 16:23.112
-IT'S A BEAR.

16:25.941 --> 16:28.074
YOU KNOW, BEARS ARE --
THEY'RE STRONG

16:28.204 --> 16:32.295
AND THEY'RE...FIERCE...

16:32.426 --> 16:35.385
JUST LIKE MY CARING FOR YOU.

16:37.735 --> 16:40.042
-IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

16:40.173 --> 16:43.480
-WELL, I'M GLAD YOU LIKE IT,
BECAUSE IT TOOK ME...

16:43.611 --> 16:46.048
TOOK ME A LONGTIME

16:46.179 --> 16:49.182
TO...MAKE.

16:49.312 --> 16:51.010
-WHAT'S WRONG?

16:51.140 --> 16:53.664
-NOTHIN'.

16:53.795 --> 16:55.144
-YOU IN TROUBLE WITH THE LAW?

16:55.275 --> 16:56.928
-[ CHUCKLES ] WELL,
TO BE HONEST WITH YOU,

16:57.059 --> 16:59.018
I'M NOT REALLY SUPPOSED TO...

16:59.148 --> 17:00.454
BE DOWN HERE.

17:01.890 --> 17:03.370
-'CAUSE OF YOUR PEOPLE OR MINE?

17:03.500 --> 17:05.154
-[ LAUGHS ]

17:05.285 --> 17:07.069
BOTH.

17:22.737 --> 17:24.347
-I KNOW A PLACE THAT WE CAN GO.

17:28.047 --> 17:29.657
-FOSTER, CAN I ASK YOU
A QUESTION?

17:29.787 --> 17:31.311
-ASK.

17:31.441 --> 17:34.053
-WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED TO YOU?

17:34.183 --> 17:35.924
WHEN I WAS A KID...

17:36.055 --> 17:37.839
WELL, ALL US KIDS,
WE LOOKED UP TO YOU.

17:37.969 --> 17:40.189
I MEAN, YOU WERE FUNNY.

17:40.320 --> 17:43.845
YOU WERE BIG AND STRONG
AND VITAL.

17:43.975 --> 17:46.152
NOW YOU'RE JUST BIG AND DRUNK.

17:47.283 --> 17:49.372
-WELL, I'M BIG.

17:49.503 --> 17:51.331
AND AT THE MOMENT,
I'M PRETTY DARN DRUNK.

17:51.461 --> 17:55.030
BUT I'M SOMETHING ELSE.

17:55.161 --> 17:58.077
I'M SOMETHING YOU'LL NEVER BE --

17:58.207 --> 18:02.385
LOYAL -- TO MY FAMILY,
TO OUR WAY OF LIFE.

18:02.516 --> 18:06.085
SO YOU SAY WHATEVER YOU LIKE
ABOUT ME, ALL RIGHT?

18:06.215 --> 18:08.957
I DON'T HEAR YOUR WORDS
'CAUSE YOU DRIFTED AWAY.

18:09.088 --> 18:11.742
AND NOW YOU DRIFTED ON BACK.

18:11.873 --> 18:15.964
NO, YOU AIN'T NOTHIN'
BUT A BREEZE, SON.

18:16.095 --> 18:18.706
-[ LAUGHS ]
-AND NOT MUCH MORE.

18:18.836 --> 18:20.969
-[ EXHALES ] WELL...

18:22.579 --> 18:24.886
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
WELL, THEN I TELL YOU WHAT.

18:25.016 --> 18:26.540
THIS BREEZE...
-UH-HUH?

18:26.670 --> 18:28.324
-IS ABOUT TO KICK
SOME COAL MINERS' ASS.

18:28.455 --> 18:29.630
-OH.

18:29.760 --> 18:31.240
-COME ON.
-WHAT?

18:31.371 --> 18:32.763
-COME ON, GET UP,
YOU BIG, DRUNK LUMP.

18:32.894 --> 18:34.113
YOU GONNA COME HELP ME? HMM?

18:34.243 --> 18:35.418
-YOU'RE GONNA STOP
THEM COAL BOYS

18:35.549 --> 18:37.203
ALL BY YOURSELF, YOU DUMB SHIT?

18:37.333 --> 18:40.902
-WELL, I DON'T KNOW. I MIGHT
SLOW 'EM DOWN A LITTLE BIT.

18:41.032 --> 18:42.904
COME ON.

18:43.034 --> 18:47.691
♪♪

18:52.870 --> 18:55.134
-WAIT -- WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

18:55.264 --> 18:57.266
WHO LIVES HERE?

18:57.397 --> 18:59.442
-LADY FROM MY CHURCH.

18:59.573 --> 19:01.749
[ CHUCKLES ] IT'S OKAY.

19:01.879 --> 19:03.142
SHE'S DEAD NOW.

19:05.361 --> 19:07.363
-OKAY.

19:17.373 --> 19:18.679
[ LIGHTER CLICKS ]

19:18.809 --> 19:20.768
-SHE PASSED
A COUPLE OF MONTHS AGO.

19:23.074 --> 19:25.294
I COME HERE TO READ SOMETIMES.

19:25.425 --> 19:27.818
I LIKE HOW QUIET IT IS.

19:27.949 --> 19:30.256
[ LIGHTER CLICKS ]
SIMPLE.

19:31.561 --> 19:34.042
-SIMPLE? [ LAUGHS ]

19:34.173 --> 19:36.044
YOU CALL THIS SIMPLE?

19:36.175 --> 19:37.611
-[ CHUCKLES ] I DO.

19:37.741 --> 19:39.178
[ LIGHTER CLICKS ]

19:48.752 --> 19:50.667
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

19:52.452 --> 19:54.018
-WHAT'S IT LOOKS LIKE I'M DOING?

19:54.149 --> 19:57.674
-IT LOOKS LIKE YOU'VE...

19:57.805 --> 19:59.154
GOT YOUR CLOTHES OFF.

19:59.285 --> 20:01.200
-NO.

20:03.637 --> 20:04.986
-[ CHUCKLES ]

20:08.555 --> 20:10.165
-NOW THEY'RE OFF.

20:12.602 --> 20:13.777
COME HERE.

20:13.908 --> 20:15.214
-YOU COME HERE.

20:15.344 --> 20:16.606
-COME HERE.

20:20.697 --> 20:22.221
DO YOU WANNA?

20:22.351 --> 20:24.135
-[ Whispers ] OH, YEAH.
-YEAH.

20:24.266 --> 20:26.573
-MM-HMM. HELLO.

20:26.703 --> 20:29.663
-MM-HMM. HOW MUCH?

20:29.793 --> 20:32.013
-THIS MUCH.
-[ LAUGHS ]

20:32.143 --> 20:34.102
-MMM.

20:34.233 --> 20:36.539
-TAKE THESE OFF.

20:47.158 --> 20:49.813
-[ MOANS AND LAUGHS ]

20:56.429 --> 20:59.170
WAIT. SHOES.

20:59.301 --> 21:02.261
[ SHOES THUD ]

21:02.391 --> 21:03.784
-[ WHISPERS INDISTINCTLY ]

21:03.914 --> 21:05.960
-JUST RIP 'EM.
-STOP SQUIRMIN'.

21:06.090 --> 21:09.398
-[ LAUGHS, MOANS ]
-COME HERE.

21:09.529 --> 21:14.621
[ BOTH MOANING ]

21:14.751 --> 21:17.537
♪♪

21:20.714 --> 21:22.063
-[ SPITS ]

21:23.891 --> 21:25.632
[ LAUGHS ]

21:25.762 --> 21:27.111
-YEP.

21:31.681 --> 21:35.163
[ PANTING ]

21:41.865 --> 21:43.302
NO KEYS?

21:43.432 --> 21:45.129
-NOPE. I DIDN'T THINK
THEY'D LEAVE THEM OUT.

21:45.260 --> 21:46.870
THEY'RE PROBABLY
IN THE TRAILER.

21:47.001 --> 21:50.047
BUT LUCKY FOR US...

21:50.178 --> 21:52.659
I BROUGHT THE KEY.
-UH-HUH.

21:52.789 --> 21:55.357
-WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
STAY CLOSE BEHIND ME.

21:55.488 --> 21:57.490
ANYONE SHOWS UP, YOU YELL.
OKAY?

21:57.620 --> 21:59.318
-I WILL BE RIGHT HERE.

22:09.676 --> 22:11.634
-PUT YOUR HANDS UP, FREAK!

22:11.765 --> 22:14.637
-FOSTER!
-HANDS UP NOW!

22:14.768 --> 22:16.335
GET BACK AWAY FROM THE DOOR.

22:16.465 --> 22:19.120
GET DOWN ON THE GROUND
WITH YOUR ARMS IN FRONT OF YOU.

22:19.250 --> 22:22.341
I GOT ORDERS TO SHOOT!
NOW GET DOWN!

22:22.471 --> 22:24.168
-[ GROANS ]
-COAL COMPANY WOULD PROBABLY

22:24.299 --> 22:26.736
PREFER ME SHOOTIN' YOU,
BUT BEING A GOOD CHRISTIAN MAN,

22:26.867 --> 22:29.348
I'M GONNA GIVE YOU --

22:29.478 --> 22:31.001
-[ LAUGHS ]

22:31.132 --> 22:33.917
-I GOTTA SAY, COUSIN,
THERE IS SOMETHING SO RIGHT

22:34.048 --> 22:36.572
ABOUT SEEING YOU
FACEDOWN IN THE DIRT.

22:38.269 --> 22:39.923
-WOULDN'T BE THE FIRST TIME.

22:42.839 --> 22:44.841
-OH!

22:44.972 --> 22:47.888
LET'S GO HAVE SOME FUN.

22:54.155 --> 22:55.374
[ ENGINE STARTS ]

22:55.504 --> 22:58.507
[ LIGHTS CLICK ON ]

22:58.638 --> 22:59.856
♪♪

22:59.987 --> 23:01.205
[ CLICKS ]

23:03.773 --> 23:06.820
[ ENGINE REVS ]

23:08.038 --> 23:11.259
-WHOA.
AH, HA HA.

23:12.739 --> 23:15.219
[ LAUGHS ] WHOA.

23:15.350 --> 23:18.179
H-- HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY.

23:18.309 --> 23:19.485
WHOO!

23:21.312 --> 23:24.968
[ LOUD WHIRRING ]

23:34.108 --> 23:37.764
♪♪

23:45.641 --> 23:48.427
[ CRASHING, SHATTERING ]

23:48.557 --> 23:51.734
-[ LAUGHS ] WHOO!

23:51.865 --> 23:54.824
♪♪

24:07.533 --> 24:09.796
AH!

24:19.022 --> 24:21.155
-YOU'RE MINE!

24:21.285 --> 24:23.157
[ LAUGHS ]

24:23.287 --> 24:24.593
-AHH!

24:33.167 --> 24:37.040
-OH, NO. NO, NO, NO, NO.
NO, NO. NO, NO.

24:41.697 --> 24:43.220
[ LAUGHS ]

24:45.919 --> 24:48.443
SHOW ME WHAT YOU GOT, LOSTIE!

24:49.836 --> 24:51.402
[ LOUD CLANK ]

24:51.533 --> 24:54.057
OOH!
[ GRINDING ]

24:54.188 --> 24:56.016
[ LAUGHING ]

24:56.146 --> 24:58.975
THAT'S HOW YOU DO IT.

25:02.022 --> 25:03.197
HEY --

25:03.327 --> 25:06.243
[ GLASS SHATTERS ]
OH, YOU --

25:06.374 --> 25:09.551
-I GOT YOU. I GOT YOU.

25:11.814 --> 25:14.861
-ALL RIGHT, YOU LITTLE SHIT.

25:14.991 --> 25:17.516
♪♪

25:22.564 --> 25:26.089
[ LOUD WHIRRING ]

25:27.874 --> 25:30.833
-FOSTER! FOSTER!

25:30.964 --> 25:33.793
OH, OKAY! ENOUGH!
-[ LAUGHS ]

25:33.923 --> 25:36.447
[ GLASS SHATTERS ]
-AAH!

25:36.578 --> 25:38.711
[ GRUNTING ]

25:40.539 --> 25:42.366
AAH!

25:42.497 --> 25:46.370
[ GRUNTING ]

25:46.501 --> 25:47.981
-ALL RIGHT.

26:03.692 --> 26:06.956
[ LAUGHING ]

26:07.087 --> 26:08.523
[ SHATTERS ]

26:08.654 --> 26:09.916
[ TURNS OFF ENGINE ]

26:10.046 --> 26:12.571
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

26:12.701 --> 26:14.964
-LOOKS LIKE THAT'S GAME, COUSIN.
[ LAUGHS ]

26:15.095 --> 26:17.358
-I ACCEPT MY DEFEAT WITH GRACE.

26:17.488 --> 26:19.839
-OH, WE GOT YOUR MACHINE
GOOD AND WRECKED.

26:19.969 --> 26:23.582
-SO, WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO
WITH YOURN?

26:23.712 --> 26:26.933
-OH. GOT ANY IDEAS?

26:31.067 --> 26:32.373
-[ CHUCKLES ]

26:32.503 --> 26:35.637
[ BACKHOE WHIRRING LOUDLY ]

26:46.474 --> 26:48.694
[ ENGINE IDLING ]

26:51.871 --> 26:55.439
♪♪

26:56.876 --> 26:58.791
[ GRUNTS ]

27:11.586 --> 27:14.023
-GED-GEDYAH.
-GED-GEDYAH.

27:15.634 --> 27:17.897
-COME ON!

27:25.687 --> 27:28.647
-[ LAUGHS ]

27:28.777 --> 27:30.039
HEY.

27:35.044 --> 27:36.306
HEY.

27:37.917 --> 27:39.614
OH!

27:39.745 --> 27:42.922
I KNEW YOU WOULD SCREW THIS UP.

27:43.052 --> 27:44.445
I SHOULD'VE DONE THIS MYSELF.

27:44.575 --> 27:47.143
-OH!
-OHH! [ LAUGHS ]

27:47.274 --> 27:50.625
[ LAUGHING ]
-GO ON, LOOK AT THAT!

27:50.756 --> 27:52.671
[ BOTH LAUGHING ]

27:52.801 --> 27:55.151
-OOH! OHH!
-OHH, YEAH!

27:55.282 --> 27:56.718
-WHOO-HOO!
-OHH!

27:56.849 --> 27:58.764
[ BOTH LAUGHING ]

27:58.894 --> 28:00.983
-OH, OH, OH! HEY, YOU --
-OHH!

28:01.114 --> 28:02.768
YES!
-OH, HO HO!

28:08.599 --> 28:08.687
-THEM COAL BOYS ARE GONNA SHIT
WHEN THEY SEE WHAT WE DONE.

28:10.427 --> 28:13.387
-[ LAUGHS ] YEP.
I'LL DRINK TO THAT.

28:13.517 --> 28:14.823
-[ LAUGHS ]
-HERE.

28:14.954 --> 28:16.825
-THEY ARE GONNA SHIT.

28:16.956 --> 28:18.522
-LOOK, THIS WAS
GOOD FUN AND ALL,

28:18.653 --> 28:19.959
BUT SERIOUSLY, FOSTER,

28:20.089 --> 28:22.178
YOU GOTTA STOP TRYING
TO KILL ME ALL THE TIME.

28:22.309 --> 28:24.006
-I NEVER DID.

28:24.137 --> 28:26.879
-THAT'S ALL YOU BEEN DOIN'
EVER SINCE I CAME BACK. ENOUGH.

28:27.009 --> 28:28.750
-WELL, HOW ABOUT...

28:28.881 --> 28:30.709
I'LL STOP WHAT I'M DOING SOON AS
YOU STOP WHAT YOU'RE DOING?

28:30.839 --> 28:32.493
-WHAT THE HELL AM IDOING?

28:32.623 --> 28:35.017
-YOU'RE TRYING TO TAKE
WHAT'S RIGHTFULLY MINE.

28:35.148 --> 28:38.760
I DIDN'T WANDER OFF LIKE YOU.
I STAYED. I WAS HERE.

28:38.891 --> 28:41.328
I WASN'T LOOKING AT TELEVISION.

28:41.458 --> 28:45.071
I WASN'T SLEEPING IN SOME
SOFT BED FULL OF LOSTIE PUSSY.

28:45.201 --> 28:46.637
-[ LAUGHS ]
-THIS IS MY MOUNTAIN.

28:46.768 --> 28:50.424
ALL RIGHT, THIS IS MYFAMILY!
ALL RIGHT?

28:50.554 --> 28:53.296
I'M GONNA LEAD 'EM, GODDAMN IT,
NOT YOU!

28:53.427 --> 28:57.605
-FOSTER, I'M NOT TRYING TO TAKE
WHAT'S YOURS.

28:57.736 --> 28:59.389
I'M JUST TRYING TO STOP
THESE OUTSIDERS

28:59.520 --> 29:01.130
BEFORE THERE'S NOTHING LEFT
FOR ANY OF US TO CLAIM.

29:01.261 --> 29:04.264
-[ GROANS ] ALL RIGHT.

29:04.394 --> 29:08.616
I KNOW WHAT YOU ARE TRYING
TO DO.

29:08.747 --> 29:11.924
-[ SCOFFS ]

29:12.054 --> 29:14.013
FOSTER -- AH, GODDAMN --

29:14.143 --> 29:15.623
HERE YOU GO.

29:17.364 --> 29:19.018
FOSTER!

29:19.148 --> 29:20.933
[ BOTH PANTING, MOANING ]

29:21.063 --> 29:23.413
-[ LAUGHS ]

29:23.544 --> 29:25.633
ALL RIGHT.

29:25.764 --> 29:27.200
[ SIGHS ]

29:27.330 --> 29:29.593
-WAS IT FINE?

29:29.724 --> 29:32.118
-[ LAUGHS ]

29:32.248 --> 29:33.728
-[ SIGHS ]

29:33.859 --> 29:37.384
I DID NOT SEE IT HAPPENING HERE
THE FIRST TIME.

29:37.514 --> 29:40.474
-[ GIGGLES AND SIGHS ]

29:40.604 --> 29:42.911
-I THOUGHT MAYBE IT'D BE UNDER
LIKE A BIG TREE.

29:43.042 --> 29:44.870
-[ SIGHS ]

29:45.000 --> 29:46.480
-STARS SHINING.

29:46.610 --> 29:48.569
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

29:54.401 --> 29:56.795
-HEY.

29:56.925 --> 29:59.623
WHAT'S THE MATTER? YOU OKAY?

29:59.754 --> 30:02.452
-YEAH.
-HEY.

30:02.583 --> 30:04.280
I DO SOMETHING?

30:04.411 --> 30:05.804
-MNH-MNH.

30:05.934 --> 30:07.588
JUST HAPPY.

30:07.718 --> 30:09.198
-OKAY.

30:09.329 --> 30:13.159
-[ GIGGLES ]
[ PHONE VIBRATES ]

30:13.289 --> 30:15.204
OH, SHOOT.

30:15.335 --> 30:17.598
-WHAT'S THE MATTER?
-I'M LATE.

30:17.728 --> 30:19.861
-WHAT YOU MEAN? HEY, COME ON.
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA. HEY.

30:19.992 --> 30:21.515
-HASIL, I GOTTA GO HOME.
-HEY, DON'T RUN OFF.

30:21.645 --> 30:22.995
COME ON,
WE GOTTA MAYBE TRY THIS AGAIN.

30:23.125 --> 30:25.824
-HASIL, I HAVE TO GO HOME.

30:32.743 --> 30:34.658
-YOU LOVE LIL FOSTER?

30:34.789 --> 30:36.704
-YOU KNOW I DO.

30:36.835 --> 30:40.229
-YES, BUT DOES HE HAVE YOUR LOVE
FULL AND COMPLETE?

30:40.360 --> 30:41.709
-OF COURSE, LADY RAY.

30:41.840 --> 30:46.409
-[ CHUCKLES ]
OH, CHILD, I DO ADORE YOU.

30:46.540 --> 30:50.326
THING I FOND TO MOST
IS HOW PURE YOUR SPIRIT BE.

30:50.457 --> 30:53.112
DONE SO LITTLE LYING
IN YOUR LIFE,

30:53.242 --> 30:55.636
DON'T KNOW HOW
TO DO IT PROPER AT ALL.

30:55.766 --> 30:59.074
LIL FOSTER,
HE IS STEADY AND SURE

30:59.205 --> 31:01.424
AND AS COZY AS A BLANKET.

31:01.555 --> 31:07.822
CAN'T EVER BE EXCITIN' OR NEW
OR UNKNOWN...

31:09.084 --> 31:10.694
UNLIKE OTHER OPTIONS.

31:10.825 --> 31:12.871
-[ CHUCKLES ]
THERE ARE NO OTHER OPTIONS.

31:13.001 --> 31:16.048
-OH, STOP IT, YOU.
DON'T INSULT ME.

31:16.178 --> 31:19.790
I MAY BE CLOSE TO THE GRAVE,
BUT I'M STILL A WOMAN.

31:19.921 --> 31:22.532
I CAN SEE LOVE FOR A MAN

31:22.663 --> 31:25.622
IN THE FACE OF ANOTHER
OF MY GENDER.

31:34.196 --> 31:35.589
-[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

31:37.678 --> 31:41.203
I SEE HIM ACROSS THE WAY,
I HEAR HIM TALK...

31:41.334 --> 31:42.509
MY HEART BEATS LIKE

31:42.639 --> 31:44.598
I THINK EVERYONE
ON THE MOUNTAIN CAN HEAR.

31:46.730 --> 31:51.387
I WANNA TEAR IT OUT OF MY CHEST
FOR MAKING ME A FOOL.

31:51.518 --> 31:54.260
I WANT HIM, BUT HE'LL HURT ME.

31:54.390 --> 31:56.871
HE'LL LEAVE AGAIN. I KNOW IT.

31:59.656 --> 32:03.225
BUT I STILL LOVE HIM.

32:03.356 --> 32:05.706
AND I HATE MYSELF FOR THAT.

32:09.449 --> 32:11.930
-LIL FOSTER --

32:12.060 --> 32:14.628
MY OWN GRANDSON.

32:14.758 --> 32:19.502
BIG AS A HOUSE, BUT THERE AIN'T
A MORE SWEET SOUL AMONG US.

32:19.633 --> 32:22.157
HIS PA AIN'T BEAT THE GENTLE
OUT OF HIM.

32:22.288 --> 32:26.292
HEAVEN ONLY KNOWS HE DONE TRIED.

32:28.772 --> 32:31.340
BUT YOU HURT HIM, G'WIN,

32:31.471 --> 32:34.039
HE'LL DRY UP AND BLOW AWAY.

32:38.565 --> 32:41.394
[ TV PLAYING INDISTINCTLY ]
[ LOCK CLICKS, KEYS RATTLE ]

32:48.575 --> 32:50.969
[ KEYS RATTLE ]
-WHERE YOU BEEN, BABY GIRL?

32:55.756 --> 32:57.714
-I WENT TO NAOMI'S AFTER WORK.

33:00.979 --> 33:03.938
-YOU WAS AT NAOMI'S?
-YES, SIR.

33:10.640 --> 33:13.382
-WAS THE WHITE BOY THERE
WITH YOU?

33:13.513 --> 33:14.993
-WHAT WHITE BOY?

33:15.123 --> 33:17.952
-PASTOR KING CALLED,

33:18.083 --> 33:19.736
SAID HE SAW YOU WALKING
WITH SOME WHITE BOY.

33:19.867 --> 33:21.390
-MUST'VE BEEN SOMEBODY ELSE.

33:21.521 --> 33:24.263
-HEY.

33:24.393 --> 33:25.829
YOU LYING TO ME?

33:27.266 --> 33:28.658
-NO, SIR.

33:28.789 --> 33:30.704
-THEN YOU'RE SAYING
PASTOR KING'S A LIAR?

33:30.834 --> 33:33.881
-SAYING HE'S MISTAKEN IS ALL.

33:34.012 --> 33:35.752
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]

33:35.883 --> 33:38.059
-HE BETTER BE.

33:43.673 --> 33:47.634
-THIS IS UNACCEPTABLE, NED.
COMPLETELY GODDAMN UNACCEPTABLE!

33:47.764 --> 33:49.984
-Don't think I've ever
heard you swear, Ms. Grimes.

33:50.115 --> 33:51.855
-WELL, THEN I DON'T THINK
YOU'VE BEEN LISTENING.

33:51.986 --> 33:54.684
-HOW BAD'S THE DAMAGE?
-THERE IS NOTHING BUT DAMAGE.

33:54.815 --> 33:56.034
I'M STANDING HERE LOOKIN AT

33:56.164 --> 33:57.731
HALF A MILLION DOLLARS' WORTH
OF SCRAP.

33:57.861 --> 34:00.255
-DID YOU TALK TO THE GUARD?
-They'd already taken him

34:00.386 --> 34:01.822
TO THE HOSPITAL
BY THE TIME I GOT HERE.

34:01.952 --> 34:03.606
IF HE KNOWS WHAT'S GOOD FOR HIM,
HE WILL DIE THERE.

34:03.737 --> 34:05.695
-I'LL CALL DES MILLER,
TELL HIM WE NEED NEW MACHINERY.

34:05.826 --> 34:07.045
-AND WE NEED IT NOW.

34:07.175 --> 34:08.611
WE'RE NOT GONNA LET IT
SLOW US DOWN.

34:08.742 --> 34:11.440
-SHOULD I CALL THE POLICE?
-NO, THEY'RE USELESS.

34:11.571 --> 34:13.616
THE NEW SHERIFF'S AN OXY FREAK.

34:13.747 --> 34:16.271
YOU KNOW WHAT? WE'RE GONNA
HANDLE THIS ONE ON OUR OWN.

34:19.187 --> 34:21.233
-OHH, MY SAINTED MOTHER.

34:21.363 --> 34:23.409
OH, MY POOR HEAD'S BANGING

34:23.539 --> 34:26.803
LIKE HEAVEN AND EARTH
COME CRASHING INTO EACH OTHER.

34:26.934 --> 34:30.198
MORNING, LOVEBIRDS.
Y'ALL MARRIED YET?

34:30.329 --> 34:32.766
-YOU'LL BE THE FIRST TO KNOW,
BIG FOSTER. I PROMISE.

34:32.896 --> 34:34.768
-WELL, I CERTAINLY HOPE SO,

34:34.898 --> 34:36.813
SEEING AS I'M GONNA BE
YOUR BELOVED FATHER-IN-LAW.

34:36.944 --> 34:40.817
HOW ABOUT THE TWO OF YOU CHOOSE
A CELEBRATION DAY RIGHT NOW?

34:40.948 --> 34:42.080
YEAH, I THINK YOUR KIN HERE

34:42.210 --> 34:44.256
WOULD BE VERY EXCITED
ABOUT THAT NEWS.

34:44.386 --> 34:46.084
WOULDN'T THAT BE SOME
EXCITEMENT?

34:46.214 --> 34:48.303
-HOW ABOUT YOU THINK
ON YOUR OWN LIFE

34:48.434 --> 34:50.958
AND LEAVE OURS TO US?
-COME ON, LIL FOSTER.

34:51.089 --> 34:52.699
TELL US THE WEDDIN' DAY!

34:52.829 --> 34:55.136
SURE HELP TO GET ME THINKING
IT'S ACTUALLY GONNA HAPPEN.

34:55.267 --> 34:57.617
-YEAH.
-WHOA!

34:57.747 --> 35:00.098
-[ LAUGHS ]

35:00.228 --> 35:02.535
-YOU READY?

35:02.665 --> 35:05.364
-I SUPPOSE WE SHOULD
GET ON HOME.

35:05.494 --> 35:07.017
OH, UNLESS YOU GOT SOMETHING
YOU WANNA SAY.

35:07.148 --> 35:08.802
-[ CHUCKLES ] OH, NO, MA'AM.

35:08.932 --> 35:10.456
-GUESS WE'LL BE
RUNNING ALONG THEN.

35:10.586 --> 35:13.111
-OH, NO.
OH, COME ON, YOU TWO.

35:13.241 --> 35:16.157
HEY, WE WAS ONLY LARKIN'.
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:16.288 --> 35:18.159
OHH...

35:18.290 --> 35:20.074
OH, DAMN. [ SIGHS ]

35:20.205 --> 35:22.120
OH, SOMEBODY LOOK,

35:22.250 --> 35:24.557
SEE THE TOP OF MY HEAD
AIN'T COME OFF.

35:24.687 --> 35:26.950
-GOT INTO THAT JUG GOOD
LAST NIGHT, DIDN'T YA?

35:27.081 --> 35:28.691
-ME AND ASA, WE HAD US A TIME.

35:28.822 --> 35:30.389
-YOU AND ASA?

35:30.519 --> 35:32.695
-MM-HMM. OH, WE PLAYED US
SOME RED AND BLACK.

35:32.826 --> 35:34.044
AND THEN WE DID US
SOME DRINKING,

35:34.175 --> 35:35.829
THEN WE HIED ON
DOWN THAT MOUNTAIN

35:35.959 --> 35:40.138
AND WE SMASHED UP A COUPLE
OF THEM COAL COMPANY MACHINES.

35:40.268 --> 35:43.793
-WELL, HOW'D YOU DO THAT?
-WE STARTED 'EM UP, AND BANG!

35:43.924 --> 35:45.969
OOH, YOU AIN'T NEVER HEARD
SUCH A NOISE.

35:46.100 --> 35:48.363
[ COUGHS ]
-I LIKE THE SOUND OF THAT.

35:48.494 --> 35:51.845
-I'M GONNA GO PUKE
IN THE BUSHES.

35:51.975 --> 35:53.977
SAVE ME SOME OF THAT HASH.

35:54.108 --> 35:58.678
-HEY, CUZ, I GOT ME AN IDEA.

35:58.808 --> 36:03.378
-[ SNORING ]
[ TV PLAYING INDISTINCTLY ]

36:08.122 --> 36:09.906
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

36:15.347 --> 36:17.610
[ GROANS ]

36:20.439 --> 36:21.962
[ GRUNTS ]

36:23.485 --> 36:26.314
♪♪

36:30.144 --> 36:33.016
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

36:35.280 --> 36:36.411
CALEB!

36:36.542 --> 36:38.196
CALEB?

36:38.326 --> 36:41.721
[ INSECTS CHIRPING ]

36:41.851 --> 36:45.768
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

36:45.899 --> 36:47.553
CALEB!

36:51.470 --> 36:52.775
CALEB!

36:52.906 --> 36:54.821
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

36:54.951 --> 36:57.215
♪♪

36:57.345 --> 37:01.306
PLEASE, GOD. COME ON, COME ON.
WHERE ARE YOU?

37:04.918 --> 37:07.137
CALEB! CALEB!

37:09.488 --> 37:11.577
SHIT!

37:12.839 --> 37:15.102
CALEB!

37:33.120 --> 37:34.382
[ SHIFTS GEARS ]

37:34.513 --> 37:35.644
CALEB.

37:35.775 --> 37:38.821
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

37:38.952 --> 37:40.214
CALEB.

37:41.650 --> 37:43.261
CALEB.
-HEY.

37:43.391 --> 37:47.656
-"HEY." RIGHT. "HEY."
THAT'S WHAT YOU GOTTA SAY TO ME?

37:47.787 --> 37:50.268
[ GROANS ]

37:50.398 --> 37:52.705
WHAT IN GOD'S NAME
ARE YOU DOING?

37:52.835 --> 37:54.620
-I'M WAITING FOR THE BUS.

37:54.750 --> 37:56.361
-WHAT BUS?

37:56.491 --> 37:58.188
-THE SCHOOL BUS.

37:58.319 --> 38:00.016
-CAY, IT'S 10:45 AT NIGHT.

38:00.147 --> 38:02.845
-I'M JUST DOING WHAT
MOM TOLD ME TO DO.

38:04.543 --> 38:06.153
-WHAT?

38:06.284 --> 38:09.678
-MOM TOLD ME TO GET UP
AND GO WAIT FOR THE BUS.

38:11.289 --> 38:13.247
-[ Whispers ] HEY. HEY.

38:13.378 --> 38:15.510
HEY, CA-- CALEB, WAKE UP.

38:15.641 --> 38:19.166
CALEB. CALEB, WAKE UP.
THAT'S IT.

38:19.297 --> 38:20.820
IT'S OKAY. IT'S OKAY.

38:20.950 --> 38:23.692
IT'S OKAY. IT'S OKAY.
IT'S OKAY.

38:23.823 --> 38:25.303
-WHERE ARE WE?
-IT'S ALL RIGHT.

38:25.433 --> 38:26.826
EVERYTHING'S FINE, OKAY?

38:26.956 --> 38:29.481
YOU JUST WANTED TO GET
SOME FRESH AIR. OKAY.

38:29.611 --> 38:32.266
COME HERE, COME HERE,
COME HERE, COME HERE.

38:32.397 --> 38:35.313
[ GRUNTS ]
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

38:35.443 --> 38:38.403
SHH. YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.
GOOD. GOOD.

38:39.708 --> 38:42.232
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

38:42.363 --> 38:43.669
SHH.

38:51.198 --> 38:52.678
-SO YOU'LL GIVE ME
THE THREE CAMERAS

38:52.808 --> 38:54.375
AND THE MOTION-ACTIVATED
LIGHTING, FRONT AND BACK?

38:54.506 --> 38:55.898
-YES, SIR. AND LIKE I SAID,

38:56.029 --> 38:58.118
I'M GIVING YOU
THE BEST PRICE I CAN GET YOU.

38:58.248 --> 38:59.815
-WHEN WILL THE GUARD BE HERE?

38:59.946 --> 39:02.340
-WELL, YOU WON'T NEED HIM
ONCE WE GET YOU ALL TRICKED OUT.

39:02.470 --> 39:04.516
BUT I UNDERSTAND.
IT'S BETTER SAFE THAN SORRY.

39:04.646 --> 39:07.170
HE'LL BE HERE IN ABOUT AN HOUR.
FRANK'S A GOOD MAN.

39:07.301 --> 39:10.043
-THANK YOU.
-YOU CAN REST EASY, MR. OSBORN.

39:10.173 --> 39:11.740
BY THE TIME WE'RE DONE,

39:11.871 --> 39:13.699
ANYBODY COMES WITHIN 50 FEET
OF THIS PLACE,

39:13.829 --> 39:15.440
YOU'RE GONNA KNOW.

39:18.660 --> 39:20.880
-[ CLEARS THROAT ]

39:21.010 --> 39:23.186
-OH, IS THAT FOR ME?

39:23.317 --> 39:25.493
-NO. UH, HAYLIE GRIMES HERE?

39:25.624 --> 39:28.453
-SHE'S ON THE PHONE, BUT I'LL
LET HER KNOW YOU'RE HERE.

39:30.193 --> 39:32.631
[ PUSHING BUTTONS ]

39:32.761 --> 39:35.198
YES, THE SHERIFF IS HERE.

39:35.329 --> 39:36.765
ALL RIGHT, I SURE WILL.

39:36.896 --> 39:38.071
[ HANGS UP RECEIVER ]

39:38.201 --> 39:40.073
SHE'LL BE RIGHT WITH YOU.
HAVE A SEAT.

39:44.730 --> 39:46.645
-[ SIGHS ]

39:49.822 --> 39:52.215
BREECE.
-HEY, WADE.

39:56.481 --> 39:59.135
-HOW'S LEDDA?
-GOOD.

40:00.485 --> 40:03.662
CALEB GOOD?
-YEAH, FOR THE MAIN.

40:05.446 --> 40:08.144
SO, UH...

40:08.275 --> 40:09.537
WHAT'S THE JOB YOU'RE DOING?

40:09.668 --> 40:11.887
-I'M COMMUNITY LIAISON.

40:12.018 --> 40:13.585
-WHAT DOES THAT ENTAIL?

40:13.715 --> 40:15.891
-JUST...

40:16.022 --> 40:18.067
BEING A LIAISON BETWEEN
THE COAL COMPANY

40:18.198 --> 40:20.026
AND FOLKS IN TOWN.

40:21.201 --> 40:22.811
-WHAT DOES THAT ENTAIL?

40:22.942 --> 40:26.249
-I HEAR YOU'RE THE HEAD HONCHO
UP AT HEADQUARTERS NOW.

40:26.380 --> 40:28.077
-SAD TO SAY SO.

40:28.208 --> 40:29.470
-WHAT DOES THATENTAIL?

40:30.993 --> 40:32.734
-HOW YOU MEAN?

40:34.519 --> 40:37.260
-LOOKS LIKE IT MAINLY ENTAILS
DELIVERING GIFT BASKETS.

40:37.391 --> 40:39.437
OR IS THAT EVIDENCE?
[ PHONE RINGS ]

40:39.567 --> 40:42.265
LIKE SOMEBODY STOLE IT
AND YOU RECOVERED IT?

40:42.396 --> 40:44.442
[ RECEIVER THUDS ]

40:44.572 --> 40:46.835
-MISS GRIMES SAYS YOU CAN
GO ON IN.

40:46.966 --> 40:49.447
-[ SIGHS ]

40:49.577 --> 40:52.101
-IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU, WADE.
-OH, YEAH.

40:52.232 --> 40:53.451
[ DOOR OPENS ]

40:53.581 --> 40:56.410
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]
SO, UM...

40:56.541 --> 40:58.194
THANK YOU FOR THE OFFER,
BUT, UH,

40:58.325 --> 41:01.328
WE CAN'T ACCEPT GIFTS FROM
THE PUBLIC OR, UM, STRANGERS.

41:01.459 --> 41:03.461
-I UNDERSTAND, SHERIFF.

41:03.591 --> 41:06.464
YOU'RE NEW TO THE JOB. YOU WANNA
DO EVERYTHING BY THE BOOK.

41:06.594 --> 41:09.075
-SURE. UH, I'M JUST GONNA
LEAVE THAT THERE.

41:10.424 --> 41:12.426
-IS EVERYTHING STILL IN HERE?

41:18.432 --> 41:21.304
-NO, MA'AM. I --
I ATE THEM BUTTER COOKIES.

41:21.435 --> 41:23.393
-YOU MEAN...

41:23.524 --> 41:25.308
THESEBUTTER COOKIES?

41:25.439 --> 41:28.398
-THERE WAS...
THERE WAS A SECOND PACKAGE.

41:28.529 --> 41:30.531
-JUST SO YOU KNOW, SHERIFF,

41:30.662 --> 41:32.228
WE HAD SOME TROUBLE
AT OUR CONSTRUCTION SITE

41:32.359 --> 41:33.665
THE OTHER NIGHT.

41:33.795 --> 41:36.102
TWO OF OUR VEHICLES
WERE HEAVILY VANDALIZED.

41:36.232 --> 41:38.278
-OKAY. COME IN, FILE A REPORT,
AND I'LL GET ONTO IT.

41:38.408 --> 41:40.498
-OH, NO, WE'LL HANDLE IT.

41:40.628 --> 41:42.325
YOU HAVE OTHER THINGS
TO DEAL WITH.

41:42.456 --> 41:44.502
I KNOW HOW OVERWHELMED YOU ARE.

41:49.332 --> 41:52.248
-THINK YOU'RE PRETTY SMART.

41:52.379 --> 41:55.730
-WHAT?
-YOU'RE PRETTY SMART.

41:55.861 --> 41:57.819
WENT TO COLLEGE,
GOT YOUR EDUCATION,

41:57.950 --> 41:59.821
SITTING BEHIND YOUR DESK.

41:59.952 --> 42:01.475
YOU THINK YOU KNOW ME.

42:01.606 --> 42:03.521
-WELL, YES, I DO.

42:03.651 --> 42:05.435
-YOU THINK YOU KNOW WHAT'S UP
ON THAT MOUNTAIN, TOO.

42:05.566 --> 42:08.526
BUT LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING.
YOU DON'T KNOW A GODDAMN THING.

42:08.656 --> 42:11.616
BECAUSE IF YOU KNEW
WHAT WAS UP THERE,

42:11.746 --> 42:14.357
YOU WOULDN'T BE CHASING
AFTER IT.

42:14.488 --> 42:18.318
YOU WOULD BE RUNNING
AS FAR AS YOU COULD POSSIBLY GO

42:18.448 --> 42:20.059
IN THE OPPOSITE DIRECTION.

42:21.364 --> 42:24.498
BUT YOU GO ON. KEEP LOOKING.
YOU'LL FIND OUT.

42:24.629 --> 42:27.153
[ DOOR OPENS ]
-ALWAYS A PLEASURE!

42:33.768 --> 42:35.204
[ PILLS RATTLING ]

42:35.335 --> 42:36.597
[ Whispers ] SIX...

42:43.648 --> 42:45.563
-[ SIGHS ]

42:45.693 --> 42:47.390
WHAT YOU THINK?

42:47.521 --> 42:49.305
-I THINK WE GONNA MAKE US
SOME NOISE.

42:49.436 --> 42:52.657
-YEAH. GO DOWN AND HAVE
A LITTLE BIT OF FUN HERE.

42:52.787 --> 42:54.310
ALL RIGHT.

43:00.665 --> 43:03.102
YOU SEE KEYS?

43:03.232 --> 43:06.018
-NO. LET'S CHECK THE OTHER ONE.

43:08.890 --> 43:11.589
-OHH... [ EXHALES ]

43:11.719 --> 43:13.765
I AIN'T NEVER DRIVEN
ANYTHING THIS BIG BEFORE.

43:13.895 --> 43:17.420
-WHO CARES ABOUT DRIVING, MAN?
I WANNA DO SOME CRASHIN'.

43:17.551 --> 43:19.509
-YEAH, COUSIN. YOU SAID THAT.

43:19.640 --> 43:20.815
[ GUNSHOT ]
-HUH?

43:20.946 --> 43:22.121
[ GUNFIRE ]
ENOCH, GET DOWN!

43:22.251 --> 43:23.426
-AAH!
-ENOCH! ENOCH!

43:23.557 --> 43:24.732
-OH! DAMN, I'M SHOT!

43:24.863 --> 43:27.169
-COME ON, BUDDY!
-AAH! HE GOT MY LEG, MAN!

43:27.300 --> 43:28.736
[ GRUNTING ]

43:28.867 --> 43:30.956
-THE HELL WITH THIS SHIT!
-NO! HEY, HELP ME!

43:31.086 --> 43:32.479
-HELP YOUR OWN SELF!

43:32.610 --> 43:34.524
-AAH!
[ GUNFIRE CONTINUES ]

43:35.787 --> 43:39.007
-[ GRUNTS ]
[ STARTS ENGINE ]

43:39.138 --> 43:40.705
[ GUNFIRE CONTINUES ]

43:44.926 --> 43:48.147
♪♪

43:59.201 --> 44:02.204
♪♪

44:24.270 --> 44:27.273
[ TWISTING ]

44:34.367 --> 44:36.848
[ LIQUID POURING ]

44:51.427 --> 44:52.733
-[ SNIFFS ]

44:52.864 --> 44:54.169
[ SNAPS CAP ]

44:57.303 --> 44:59.653
[ SNIFFS ]
[ TOOTHBRUSH CLATTERS ]

45:01.002 --> 45:03.613
[ INHALES SHARPLY ] AAH!

45:03.744 --> 45:05.224
VANESSA!

45:05.354 --> 45:07.705
[ EXHALES ]

45:07.835 --> 45:09.794
VANESSA!

45:09.924 --> 45:11.404
AAH!

45:11.534 --> 45:14.581
SOMEBODY HELP ME!
AAH! SHIT!

45:14.712 --> 45:16.322
VANESSA!

45:16.452 --> 45:19.499
AAH! AAH! HEY!
